    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-10-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="119" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-10-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 6,
                            1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my telegrams to you of the 16th
                        ultimo and the 3d instant, relative to negotiations for carrying into effect
                        the regulations proposed by the Bering Sea Arbitration Tribunal, I inclose,
                        as of probable use to-you in conducting the business, a copy of a
                            letter,<note n="1" xml:id="d119fn1">See Senate Ex. Doc. No. 67,
                            Fifty-third Congress, third session, page 23.</note> dated the 4th
                        ultimo, from the Hon. E. J. Phelps, commenting on the award made by the
                        arbitrators; also a copy of suggestions<note n="2" xml:id="d119fn2">The same
                            document, page 26.</note> by Mr. James C. Carter on certain branches of
                        the subject.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
